<DOC><DOCNO> AP900326-0101 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-26-90 1411EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Netherlands-Bomb     03-26 0176</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Netherlands-Bomb,0180</SECOND><HEAD>Bomb Attack on Dutch Justice Ministry</HEAD><DATELINE>THE HAGUE, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A bomb exploded in the DutchJustice Ministry early Monday, and police said a group protestingthe death almost a decade ago of a hunger striker claimedresponsibility.   The bomb went off at about 4 a.m. It caused no injuries, butdamage was estimated at $175,000, according to police spokeswomanBernadette Maclean.   Later Monday, a group identifying itself as the RevolutionaryAnti-Racist Action claimed responsibility for the incident inletters sent to an Amsterdam newspaper and the Dutch national newsagency, according to Ms. Maclean.   She quoted the letter as saying that the bomb attack was toprotest the death in 1982 of a Spanish hunger striker identified asCrespo Galendo. The circumstances of Galendo's death could notimmediately be established.   The same organization claimed responsibility earlier this monthfor arson attacks on two Dutch military police stations.   In December, Spanish government buildings here were targeted inbomb attacks that were believed to have been staged by ETA, theBasque separatist organization.</TEXT></DOC>